                            <comment id="13088449" author="wajam" created="Sun, 21 Aug 2011 20:46:42 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;If what we want is that the keyspace name is case-sensitive and system &amp;lt;&amp;gt; SYSTEM, patch attached! Otherwise, I have no clue &lt;img class=&quot;emoticon&quot; src=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/images/icons/emoticons/smile.png&quot; height=&quot;16&quot; width=&quot;16&quot; align=&quot;absmiddle&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; border=&quot;0&quot;/&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13088840" author="jbellis" created="Mon, 22 Aug 2011 17:40:57 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The real problem is allowing the create in the first place.  v2 attached.  From the comments: &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;        &lt;span class=&quot;code-comment&quot;&gt;// keyspace names must be unique &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;case&lt;/span&gt;-insensitively because the keyspace name beomes the directory
&lt;/span&gt;        &lt;span class=&quot;code-comment&quot;&gt;// where we store CF sstables.  Names that differ only in &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;case&lt;/span&gt; would thus cause problems on
&lt;/span&gt;        &lt;span class=&quot;code-comment&quot;&gt;// &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;case&lt;/span&gt;-insensitive filesystems (NTFS, most installations of HFS+).&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;(Also renamed the ListAccess methods to SchemaAccess.)&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
